James,

One of the substantial design changes in JUnit 4 is there is no longer a
Composite hierarchy of tests. The arbitrary depth and ability to create
custom TestSuites and insert TestDecorators made writing runners difficult,
especially re-run. Instead you now pass a flat array of test classes to
JUnitCore to run a suite of tests. The RunListener doesn&#39;t currently provide
notification when one of those classes starts and stops. I can imagine such
notification might be useful, but I don&#39;t want to put it in without more
justification than that. Can you distill your wishes into a test case?

Sincerely yours,

Kent Beck
Three Rivers Institute 

